Film grain for video. Save the video using Encode and Save with a high rate for keeping the grain. Be aware many third party app will compress your video files affecting how grain is displayed. I very much appreciate your help Glenn Upgraded and Kamalky Laureano!

In total more than 150 new presets: Added new Wavegod presets by Rahkim Brown Instagram: wavegodphotography Added new Enhance2 Byron Shelley Duotone2 Stone Lomage and Divided presets. Some improvements on the waveform.

LUT intensity. Touch down an already selected preset It affects only the LUT. kind of the same as it works on the camera There is also an Overall Intensity in Adjusts but that one affects all adjustments. This LUT intensity value is also registered in Profiles in the same way as any adjustment so if you use profiles just remember that. RGB parade in supported devices. Very grateful to all of you at the Facebook group! Big thanks to Glenn Upgraded for requesting many of these features.

Camera changes: Alternative camera view for iPhone X by default as it solves some issues. You can still switch at Settings app VideoLUT 4K recording by default if available in your device Tap for focus

In Settings App search for Video LUT there are new 2 switches: Enable 4K recording with the camera if available in your device Change Camera to OpenGL renderer if you have problems displaying the camera.

Solves a problem with the camera in iPhone X Solves a problem when exporting cubes to iCloud while processing videos. Some important info when exporting cubes to DropBox: You have to enable DropBox in Files app: 1. Open Files App 2. Enable the switch besides DropBox personal It has to be green enabled 3. Press Done on top 4. Close Video LUT if open Open Video LUT 5. Select your LUT 6. Happy exporting!
Open Camera: Record your videos with your favorites LUTs!

Now you can import and export .cube files from to iCloud and other online storage services. For importing use menu: Import or Admin:Import.Imported files will appear under Imported .CUBE For exporting current LUT: use Save: Export cube 16 or 32.
